header.description:
(Required) NOTE!: Signature generation was changed since v1

A HMAC-SHA256 signature in `base64` encoded format. The signature is created from the request payload and the app's client secret.

E.g. based on following parameters

```
body = {
    "key": "valüe",
    "key2": {
        "name": "Jåhn Gätes",
        "address": "Test Street",
        "colors": ["Red", "Blue"]
    }
}
secret = "topSecret"
```

it will always generate the following signature if done correctly, regardless of technology used.

```
7aVthZdRg8OZw9MDQxe7DfTdsnTOvi68Lfuq3ynaBj4=
```

Python example:

```
import base64
import hashlib
import hmac
import json

body = {
    "key": "valüe",
    "key2": {
        "name": "Jåhn Gätes",
        "address": "Test Street",
        "colors": ["Red", "Blue"]
    }
}
client_secret = "topSecret"

body_string = json.dumps(
    body,
    sort_keys=True,
    ensure_ascii=False,
    separators=(",", ":")
)

digest = hmac.new(
    client_secret.encode("utf-8"),
    body_string.encode("utf-8"),
    hashlib.sha256
).digest()

# return the digest in base64 encoded format:
signature = base64.b64encode(digest).decode()

print(signature)  # 7aVthZdRg8OZw9MDQxe7DfTdsnTOvi68Lfuq3ynaBj4=
```

Let's explain once which parameters to use to generate correct `body_string`. 
`sort_keys=True` means that the output of dictionaries will be sorted by keys, `separators=(',', ':')` means there is no spaces between separators. `ensure_ascii=False` is used to keep non-ASCII characters as-is rather than escaping them; e.g. keep "åäö" rather than escaping to "\\u00e5\\u00e4\\u00f6".

JavaScript example:

```
const jsSHA = require("jssha");
const stringify = require("json-stable-stringify");

const body = {
  "key": "valüe",
  "key2": {
    "name": "Jåhn Gätes",
    "address": "Test Street",
    "colors": ["Red", "Blue"]
  }
};

const clientSecret = "client_secret";

// Sort keys and stringify.
// Note "json-stable-stringify" is used
const bodyString = stringify(body);

const shaObj = new jsSHA(
  "SHA-256", 
  "TEXT", 
  { encoding: "UTF8" }
);

shaObj.setHMACKey(clientSecret, "TEXT");
shaObj.update(bodyString);

// Signature in base64 to use in request
const signature = shaObj.getHMAC("B64");

console.log(signature) // 7aVthZdRg8OZw9MDQxe7DfTdsnTOvi68Lfuq3ynaBj4=
```

PHP example:

```
<?php

function ksortRecursive(&$array) {
    if (is_array($array)) {
        ksort($array);
        foreach ($array as &$arr) {
            ksortRecursive($arr);
        }
    }
}

$body = array(
  "key" => "valüe",
  "key2" => array(
    "name" => "Jåhn Gätes",
    "address" => "Test Street",
    "colors" => array("Red", "Blue")
  )
);

$client_secret = "topSecret";

ksortRecursive($body);

$body_string = json_encode(
   $body,   
   JSON_UNESCAPED_UNICODE
);

$signature = base64_encode(
  hash_hmac(
    'sha256',
        $body_string,
        $client_secret,
        true
  )
);

echo($signature . "\n"); # 7aVthZdRg8OZw9MDQxe7DfTdsnTOvi68Lfuq3ynaBj4=
```

